    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** (74.01) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) anchor the lineup as our primary offensive engines. **Corbin Carroll** thrives against Brandon Sproat, benefiting from a balanced profile bolstered by his high xwOBA and a prime #3 spot, while **Vinnie Pasquantino** faces a favorable environment against Luis Severino. The park factors and SP skill metrics significantly elevate **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who is primed for a high-efficiency outing. Similarly, **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72) and **Josh Naylor** (71.58) provide substantial depth; **Tyler Soderstrom** gains massive utility from a friendly park factor and a solid platoon advantage against Michael Wacha, while **Josh Naylor** benefits from favorable SP skill metrics against Taj Bradley.\n\nStrategic edges are pervasive across the middle tier, notably with **Kyle Karros** (63.06) and **Brice Turang** (62.85). **Kyle Karros** is a strong play thanks to a combination of a weak opposing arm in Brandon Williamson and wind assistance, while **Trevor Story** (61.48) is a fascinating start due to his elite BvP history against Lauer, which provides a high-upside floor despite moderate raw projections. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Alex Freeland** (47.61), who finished just shy of the cutoff. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility, the optimizer favored the specific platoon alignments and park-adjusted floors of our current utility starters, relegating him to the bench to preserve our limited game caps.\n\nWe are monitoring several \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Brice Turang**, **James Wood**, **Corbin Carroll**, and **Tyler Soderstrom**; should any of these players shift drastically down the order, their daily efficiency scores will require re-evaluation. Additionally, be wary of the matchups for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Jose Caballero**, as both players are facing Eovaldi\u2014an elite arm who suppresses their overall scoring potential. We are prioritizing speed and high-contact profiles today to maximize our 5x5 potential, keeping **Austin Riley** and **Travis Bazzana** ready on the bench if late-breaking injury news forces a rotation.",
